- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the diffusion of contagions on a multiplex network topology, which is a type of social and information network. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a model to simulate the diffusion of contagions, which can be seen as a software engineering problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the interdependencies between different graph structures, which can be seen as a systems and control problem. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is a possible category as the paper deals with the interaction between different contagions and their impact on diffusion, which can be seen as a multi-agent system problem. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes a model that simulates the diffusion of contagions, which can be seen as a type of evolutionary computing problem.
